cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language generation and storytelling. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a reinforcement learning framework for generating stories. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to optimize the story generation process. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper uses the Visual Storytelling Dataset (VIST) for evaluation. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes new assessment criteria for evaluating the quality of generated stories.
